msgid "Returns 8.3 Filename (SFN) representation of path"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package.py:docstring of
#: spack.llnl.util.filesystem.windows_sfn:4
msgid ""
"8.3 Filenames (SFN or short filename) is a file naming convention used prior "
"to Win95 that Windows still (and will continue to) support. This convention "
"caps filenames at 8 characters, and most importantly does not allow for "
"spaces in addition to other specifications. The scheme is generally the same "
"as a normal Windows file scheme, but all spaces are removed and the filename "
"is capped at 6 characters. The remaining characters are replaced with ~N "
"where N is the number file in a directory that a given file represents i.e. "
"Program Files and Program Files (x86) would be PROGRA~1 and PROGRA~2 "
"respectively. Further, all file/directory names are all caps (although "
"modern Windows is case insensitive in practice). Conversion is accomplished "
"by fileapi.h GetShortPathNameW"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_spack_root/lib/spack/spack/package.py:docstring of
